HEADWORD: Cutwork
<hw>Cut"work`</hw> <pr>(k⟦ucr⟧t"w⟦ucir⟧rk`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Fine Arts)</fld> <def>An ancient term for embroidery, esp. applied
to the earliest form of lace, or to that early embroidery on linen and
the like, from which the manufacture of lace was developed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

